STELLENBOSCH FC have announced the signing of two new players. Having already signed Venezuelan forward Juan Ortiz last month, the has added another player in the first team, in defensive midfielder Sibongiseni Mthethwa who joins from GladAfrica Championship side Black Leopards. The club also confirmed the arrival of youngster, Shaun Morgan (17) who will join the club Diski Challenge team. "We are delighted to announce the signing of Sibongiseni 'The Ox' Mthethwa. Welcome Ox Ox," the club said. ?????????????????? ??We are delighted to announce the signing of Sibongiseni 'The Ox' Mthethwa. Welcome Ox ??#StellenboschFC #ProudlyStellenbosch ?? pic.twitter.com/BarbscW9yy  ?????????????????? ??We are delighted to announce the signing of Obarate Shaun Morgan (17) on an apprenticeship contract with the club.Welcome Shaun!#StellenboschFC #ProudlyStellenbosch ?? pic.twitter.com/wuCpK7BpZS   